          "id": "medquad-61588822be739e9b",
          "front": "How many people are affected by achondrogenesis ?",
          "back": "Achondrogenesis types 1A and 1B are rare genetic disorders; their incidence is unknown. Combined, achondrogenesis type 2 and hypochondrogenesis (a similar skeletal disorder) occur in 1 in 40,000 to 60,000 newborns."
