          "id": "medquad-dcd8e77ae23539d2",
          "front": "Is acromicric dysplasia inherited ?",
          "back": "Acromicric dysplasia is an autosomal dominant condition, which means one copy of the altered gene in each cell is sufficient to cause the disorder. Most cases result from new mutations in the gene and occur in people with no history of the disorder in their family. In other cases, an affected person inherits the mutation from one affected parent."
