          "front": "What are the treatments for acute promyelocytic leukemia ?",
          "back": "These resources address the diagnosis or management of acute promyelocytic leukemia:  - American Cancer Society: Diagnosis of Acute Myeloid Leukemia  - American Cancer Society: Treatment of Acute Promyelocytic (M3) Leukemia  - Genetic Testing Registry: Acute promyelocytic leukemia  - MedlinePlus Encyclopedia: Acute Myeloid Leukemia  - National Cancer Institute: Adult Acute Myeloid Leukemia Treatment  - National Cancer Institute: Leukemia  - National Heart Lung and Blood Institute: Bone Marrow Tests   These resources from MedlinePlus offer information about the diagnosis and management of various health conditions:  - Diagnostic Tests  - Drug Therapy  - Surgery and Rehabilitation  - Genetic Counseling   - Palliative Care"
