          "title": "How many people are affected by actin-accumulation myopathy ?",
          "content": "Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals. Because it is so uncommon, researchers do not have a clear understanding of how many people are affected by this disorder. The exact prevalence remains unknown, which means that more studies are needed to learn about this condition and its impact on those who have it.\nContext recap: Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals. Because it is so uncommon, researchers do not have a clear understanding of how many people are affected by this disorder. The exact prevalence remains unknown, which means that more studies are needed to learn about this condition and its impact on those who have it.\nContext recap: Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals. Because it is so uncommon, researchers do not have a clear understanding of how many people are affected by this disorder. The exact prevalence remains unknown, which means that more studies are needed to learn about this condition and its impact on those who have it. Context recap: Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals.\nWhy this matters: How many people are affected by actin-accumulation myopathy ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Medical Genetics (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.\nContext recap: Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals. Because it is so uncommon, researchers do not have a clear understanding of how many people are affected by this disorder. The exact prevalence remains unknown, which means that more studies are needed to learn about this condition and its impact on those who have it. Context recap: Actin-accumulation myopathy is a rare condition that has only been identified in a small number of individuals.\nWhy this matters: How many people are affected by actin-accumulation myopathy ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Medical Genetics (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.",
