          "title": "How many people are affected by Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome ?",
          "content": "Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it.\nContext recap: Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it.\nContext recap: Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it. Context recap: Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it.\nContext recap: Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it. Context recap: Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is considered a rare genetic disorder, and while it is known to affect some individuals, the exact number of people impacted by this condition is not clearly defined. This means that researchers are still working to understand how many people are living with this syndrome, as it may not be diagnosed in everyone who has it.\nWhy this matters: How many people are affected by Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Medical Genetics (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.",
