          "title": "How many people are affected by argininosuccinic aciduria ?",
          "content": "Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management.\nContext recap: Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management.\nContext recap: Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management. Context recap: Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management.\nContext recap: Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management. Context recap: Argininosuccinic aciduria is a rare condition that affects approximately 1 in every 70,000 newborns. This means that while it is not very common, it does occur, and awareness of the condition is important for early diagnosis and management.\nWhy this matters: How many people are affected by argininosuccinic aciduria ? helps learners in Science connect ideas from Medical Genetics (Medical Curriculum) to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification.",
