          "id": "medquad-a9208e178544cc67",
          "front": "How many people are affected by Canavan disease ?",
          "back": "While this condition occurs in people of all ethnic backgrounds, it is most common in people of Ashkenazi (eastern and central European) Jewish heritage. Studies suggest that this disorder affects 1 in 6,400 to 13,500 people in the Ashkenazi Jewish population. The incidence in other populations is unknown."
