          "id": "medquad-15e3c6ff9460782d",
          "front": "Is celiac disease inherited ?",
          "back": "Celiac disease tends to cluster in families. Parents, siblings, or children (first-degree relatives) of people with celiac disease have between a 4 and 15 percent chance of developing the disorder. However, the inheritance pattern is unknown."
