          "id": "medquad-098b454c26d4e878",
          "front": "How many people are affected by Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease ?",
          "back": "Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease is the most common inherited disorder that involves the peripheral nerves, affecting an estimated 150,000 people in the United States. It occurs in populations worldwide with a prevalence of about 1 in 2,500 individuals."
